      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; simulation setup reviewed by senior analyst.",
      "rationale": "At Model Risk Level 2, formal use error assessment is not required. Simulation setup files were reviewed by a senior CFD analyst with 10+ years of cardiovascular device experience. Boundary condition specification and turbulence model selection were confirmed as appropriate for the operating regime."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Selected turbulence model (SST k-omega) and hemolysis power-law model are justified by literature precedent for rotating blood-contacting devices at the Reynolds numbers present in the COU.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on documented superior performance for rotating machinery with adverse pressure gradients. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model was applied as implemented by Fraser et al. (2012), which is the predominant approach in FDA-cited literature for centrifugal pump hemolysis prediction. Model form uncertainty is considered acceptable at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
